casebody.data:
No. 11,

Original.

United States v. Louisiana. Jack P. F. Gremillion, Attorney General, W. Scott Wilkinson, Edward M. Carmouche and John L. Madden, Special Assistant Attorneys General, and Bailey Walsh for the State of Louisiana. Attorney General Brownell, Solicitor General Rankin, Oscar H. Davis, John F. Davis and George S. Swarth for the United States.

The motion to dismiss on jurisdictional grounds is denied. The motion for entry of default and for leave to proceed ex parte is denied. The State of Louisiana is directed to file an answer on the merits within 30 days.

The Chief Justice took no part in the consideration or decision of these motions, or order of the Court.
